page.title: 15Heslington Tilmire
page.content: {Line B:}The northern edge of the Tilmire:_ This area was one hundred metres south of the previous transect. The land was marshy with clumps of reeds,sedges and rough grasses.We tested the soil and discovered it was dark, dense and acid. We found fewer flying insects and few open flowering plants. Here is a list of our findings-{Grasses-}common rush, horsetail,rye, purple moor, couch, rough meadow, red fescue, black bog rush,matt, soft brome. { Plants, shrubs,trees:-}creeping buttercup, water mint, thistle, clover, lady's bedstraw. {Insects:_}devils coach horse, blood red ant, black ant, fruit fly, frog hopper, earthworm, greenfly, garden spider, grasshopper, emperor moth caterpillar, crab spider.
